OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FZambians urged to leave    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ftowns to curb deadly       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fcholera                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Zambian President Hakainde Hichilema   
OL,6, has urged people to relocate from towns
OL,7, to villages following the deaths of    
OL,8, about 300 people in a cholera outbreak.
OL,10,FPoor sanitation in some densely        
OL,11,Fpopulated urban areas was a good       
OL,12,Fbreeding ground for cholera, he said.  
OL,14,FTo decongest major towns, residents    
OL,15,Fshould relocate to rural areas where   
OL,16,Fthere was enough space and "perfect    
OL,17,Fsanitation", Mr Hichilema added.       
OL,19,FMore than 7,500 cholera cases have been
OL,20,Freported nationwide since last October.
